  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.01.Story">Grandpa Doorstache remembers the days of ages past,
when there was no lack of warmth or laughter.</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.02.Story">A moonlit window bathes the kitchen with a pale, blue glow.
GingerBrave\'s adventure began with his decision to reach
this window and escape from the clutches of the witch!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.03.Story">Deep within the oven, it feels as if the flames and heat
will consume everything. Only the most fearless and
courageous of Cookies was able to make a grand escape!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.04.Story">Wizard Cookie vowed to never give up his research into replicating Life Potions. But every once in a while, a few essential ingredients went missing, as if someone was deliberately hiding them... A ghost, perhaps?</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.05.Story">Wizard Cookie succeeded in conjuring a cauldron full of Life Potions! His calculations may have been a tad off since he created a bit too much to handle, but nonetheless, a job well done!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.06.Story">Four Cookies on an epic quest! Let\'s march forward
and embark on an... Wait, is someone watching us?
... Nah, probably not!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.07.Story">GingerDozer has been detained by Sheriff Whiskerton!
Bad kitty! BAD KITTY!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.08.Story">Unlike most Cookies, GingerDozer seems happy to hear about the witch? Are you still sleepy...???</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.09.Story">Cheesehaven is an incredibly busy place and the Cookies have learned first-hand just how busy it can be. But seeing the customers enjoying the evening did bring a smile to everyone\'s faces.</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.10.Story">GingerDozer has been captured by Sheriff Whiskerton once more. Don\'t worry, GingerDozer! We\'re coming for you!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.11.Story">The Cookies are off to rescue GingerDozer! Rescuing a friend is more important than escaping from the castle!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.12.Story">Our tale begins deep within the spooky, eerie witch\'s castle...</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.13.Story">GingerBrave is awakened by a cheery voice: \"Oh! There\'s an exhausted, crumbly Cookie here! Wakey-wakey!\"</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.14.Story">Sheriff Whiskerton has captured GingerDozer!
On what charge?! Bad kitty!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep01.15.Story">GingerDozer is still being detained by, a now very angry, Sheriff Whiskerton! Time is of the essence!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep02.01.Story">Sachertorte Cookie has booked the best seat in the Grand Cabinet Hotel\'s auction house. And she\'s not willing to give it up.</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep02.02.Story">The auction house is abuzz with whispers and murmurs. The marvelous and regal Marble Danish Cookie is attending tonight\'s auction!</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep02.03.Story">When a prideful Cookie realized the error of his ways, he extended a heartfelt apology with a deep bow, another Cookie\'s cold heart began to thaw.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialRoom.Ep02.Hotellobby001.Title">Little Giant\'s Watch</string>
