  <string name="$Neighbor.0052.Story">A cheerful Choco Mushroom Farmer. They are a great friend to have around.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0053.Story">A hearty Grape Mushroom Farmer. Hopefully you\'ll get along!</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0054.Story">A down-to-earth Strawberry Mushroom Farmer. They seem familiar somehow...</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0055.Story">Bookworm Tomato. He\'s a great friend to have around.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0056.Story">Freshy Tomato. It seems he\'s been here for a long time.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0057.Story">Crunchy Tomato. No one knows where he came from...</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0058.Story">Sweet Pea Fan Club. They seem familiar somehow...</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0059.Story">Red Bean Fan Club. No one knows where they came from...</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0060.Story">Corn Kernel Fan Club. It seems they\'ve been here for a long time.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0061.Story">The rock star himself, B. Rock\'n 51. Hopefully you\'ll get along!</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0062.Story">The disco star himself, Disco Legend B. R. Olli. He seems familiar somehow...</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0063.Story">The folksinging legend himself, Folksinger Brock \"Ole\" Lay. He\'s a great friend to have around.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0064.Story">The Twin Cherry Ladies, Scarlet &amp; Rose. It seems they\'ve been here for a long time.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0065.Story">The Twin Berry Ladies, Berry &amp; Cherry. Hopefully you\'ll get along!</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0066.Story">The Soda Cherry Ladies, Carmine &amp; Vermillion. These two are great friends to have around.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0067.Story">This tiny, cheery tomato firmly believes she is actually a cherry. Yes, a cherry... the fruit. But also, she\'s a cherry who wears a cherry atop her head. Fancy that! Anyone who objects will have to sit through one of her patented \"tomato fruitology\" lectures! But when no one else is around, Cheery Cherry Tomato wonders why there\'s an air of tart aromas in her vicinity, when they should be sweet and fruity.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0068.Story">Though it may look like this tomato would taste perfectly sweet and sour, this grumpy resident is actually super bitter! Ever since she was a small, green tomato who had yet to ripen, she hated being mistaken for a grape. Perhaps this is why she developed a habit of introducing herself as a vegetable as soon as she learned to talk. If you don\'t want to offend this little friend, you better be careful not to call her the wrong name!</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0069.Story">This fussy tomato grew up in the far corner of the garden, bathed in the warmth of the afternoon sun. The abundant sunlight turned the tomato a healthy yellowish-orange hue, so she started to believe she was actually an orange. This adorable friend has been showing up to the Fruit Community Meetings ever since, but none of the other members have the heart to tell her the truth.</string>
  <string name="$Neighbor.0070.Story">Frightened by the huge Churro Golem\'s roaring howl? If so, you\'ve completely misunderstood this gentle giant! If you\'re curious and want to see the Churro Golem\'s true form, try approaching it slowly with a handful of Sugar Powder. Watch its eyes widen as it peeps out a cute squeal!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Floor.001.Story">A fireplace created by stacking well-baked biscuits. Light it, and the room will be filled with a pleasant, sweet fragrance.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Floor.002.Story">An armchair sofa made out of slices of soft bread and sweet jam. It\'s hard to sit in this without feeling sleepy.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Floor.003.Story">A bag filled with sweets, packed by GingerBrave to share with all his Cookie friends one day!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Floor.004.Story">A crispy biscuit table. A great choice for decorating any room.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Floor.005.Story">A round stall for storing umbrellas. It seems quite handy to keep around.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Floor.006.Story">A seat made with a combination of chocolate and jam. It probably goes well anywhere you place it.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Ceil.001.Story">A lamp made out of conch-shaped bread. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Wall.001.Story">Shelves made out of roll cake. Who wouldn\'t want them in their room?</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Wall.002.Story">A pretzel-themed window. Give your view on the world a twist with this decor!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Wall.003.Story">Every thrilling adventure GingerBrave heads out on starts by opening this!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Rug.001.Story">A square rug made out of a handkerchief. Any room would look cozier with it!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Rug.002.Story">A round linen rug. Try decorating a room with it!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Hanger.001.Story">A laced curtain. Try it out and see where it fits the best!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.Deck.001.Story">Thanks to the floor having faded due to frequent use, it has a somewhat cozy feeling to it!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0001.WP.001.Story">Bricks made out of hardened bread. It looks delicious, but you probably shouldn\'t eat it.</string>
