  <string name="$Journal.Ep00.Ch01.SQuest00">Witch\'s Castle</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep00.Ch01.SQuest00.Summary">A shadowy figure, clutching an inherited recipe of old, enters the castle. Soon after, the ancient oven awakens from its slumber...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep00.Ch01.SQuest01.Summary">A freshly-baked Cookie has escaped from the oven! While fleeing from the clutches of the terrifying witch, the Cookie fell outside the castle, but is saved by a mysterious, radiant wanderer...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep00.Ch01.SQuest02.Summary">The escaped Cookie has met Witchberry Cookie, who reveals that this place is the terrifying witch\'s castle. The freshly-baked Cookie sees an open window and vows to escape through it!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest01.Summary">Our new friend, the freshly-baked Cookie, has fixed the stairs to make his way up the castle. Already, he\'s making an impact on the castle, little by little!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest02.Summary">The escaped Cookie has met Grandpa Doorstache, whose mouth has been frozen shut! Our friend decides to thaw the surrounding rooms to help Grandpa Doorstache speak normally.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest03.Summary">Grandpa Doorstache can speak once more, thanks to our Cookie friend. The hearty doorkeeper warns the Cookie to walk gingerly yet bravely. Inspired by these words, Cookie decides to give himself the name, \"GingerBrave.\"</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest04.Summary">GingerBrave suddenly feels dizzy and falls unconscious. Another Cookie, GingerBright, discovers our unconscious friend and gives him a Life Potion. Always remember: Life Potions are key to preventing staleness.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest05.Summary">GingerBright is certain following GingerBrave on an adventure will lead to all sorts of fun! The two Cookies decide to team up and find a way out of the castle.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest06.Summary">Our friends meet the shy Strawberry Cookie and a talking treasure chest... Er, correction, Wizard Cookie, who is trapped inside the chest. Apparently, Wizard Cookie is conducting research on a spell to create Life Potions?!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest07.Summary">Wizard Cookie succeeded in conjuring a cauldron filled to the brim with Life Potion, perhaps a bit too successful! The Cookies tried to store as much Life Potion as they could into empty vials.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest08.Summary">The four Cookies decide to travel together. Each has their own reason for embarking on this adventure, but they all agree that it will be better to work as a team!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest09.Summary">\"Waaah! Go away!\" The group witnessed a small Cookie being harassed by a huge cat! Don\'t worry, we\'ll save you!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest10.Summary">The team rescued the cute and adorable GingerDozer. But after learning of the witch\'s return, GingerDozer is... smiling?</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch01.SQuest11.Summary">Our friends continue their journey, but are on the verge of starving. Suddenly, a delicious, savory aroma wafts from somewhere unknown. They eagerly seek the aroma\'s source!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch02.SQuest01.Summary">The Cookies have discovered Cheesehaven, the greatest tavern in the Witch\'s Kitchen. But it\'s in danger of closing down permanently... Our friends decide to help its owner, the Cheesemaster, reopen the tavern!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch02.SQuest02.Summary">GingerBrave and friends have successfully helped the Cheesemaster handle a full house. After a busy night, and a hearty meal, GingerDozer seems sleepier than ever.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch02.SQuest03.Summary">The team chats deep into the night. It seems like they\'ll go their separate ways once they make it outside the window.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch02.SQuest04.Summary">GingerBrave and friends have finally made it to the top-most window of the witch\'s kitchen! Just as they decide to finally make their escape, a shadow approaches from behind!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch02.SQuest05.Summary">Despite the window of escape being right in front of his eyes, GingerBrave decides to rescue GingerDozer from the clutches of the Shadow Witch. GingerBright, Wizard Cookie, and Strawberry Cookie join him on the daring rescue mission!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep01.Ch02.SQuest06.Summary">The team arrives at the Grand Cabinet Hotel, only to find it empty. GingerBright rings a bell at the front desk and observe a clumsy employee running their way.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest01.Summary">The group learns that an enchanted compass is up for auction at the hotel. Maybe it can help them find GingerDozer?! Our friends decide to speak with the hotel manager to learn more.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest02.Summary">The compass is the highlight of the auction, and there\'s no way our friends can get their hands on it without bidding. The team decides to take part-time jobs to earn Sugar Coins for the big auction.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest03.Summary">In his quest to collect Sugar Coins, GingerBrave has decided to clean rooms. But some guests seem... odd. While trying to do his job, GingerBrave is kicked out of a room.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest04.Summary">Wizard Cookie\'s part-time job in the kitchen started with peeling potatoes. But alas, no magic allowed?!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest05.Summary">GingerBright has decided to work as a bellhop. She gets caught up in a slight commotion between two Cookies who seem to know each other...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest06.Summary">Strawberry Cookie, trying her hand at room service, runs into a worried guest. She musters up the courage to provide a heartfelt, honest answer and receives a generous tip as thanks!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest07.Summary">Each member of the team has completed their part-time shifts. They regroup and head to the auction with their hard-earned Sugar Coins, but are slightly delayed by a tiny mess, which they decide to help clean up.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest08.Summary">Our friends engage in a bidding war with the regal Marble Danish Cookie, who also seeks the compass. But out of nowhere, disaster strikes the auction house!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest09.Summary">GingerBrave opens his eyes to find... Witchberry Cookie? According to her, the hotel has been raided by the Apricot Jam Syndicate. Get up and save your friends, GingerBrave!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest10.Summary">GingerBrave managed to find and free his friends. The team tries to untie Marble Danish Cookie but... the rope won\'t come loose! Marble Danish Cookie asks the group to find his sword.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest11.Summary">Our friends manage to free Marble Danish Cookie and decide to rescue the staff and guests from the bandits! But they\'re ambushed!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch01.SQuest12.Summary">The manager has witnessed first-hand how strong and capable the Cookies are. He begs them to save the hotel. Our friends and Marble Danish Cookie decide to save the hotel, together!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest1.Summary">The Cookies decide to rescue the hostages, but don\'t know where to begin. Marble Danish Cookie has an idea. They visit a particularly old room first...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest2.Summary">The old, dusty room has a secret passageway! Marble Danish Cookie tells our friends that the hotel used to be his childhood home. There\'s a story behind it, but there are hostages to rescue!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest3.Summary">One of the Syndicate\'s lieutenants, Cashew, is holding the chef hostage and forcing him to taste-test a horrendous bowl of mush. Cashew challenges the Cookies to a cooking contest in exchange for the chef\'s freedom. Wizard Cookie steps up to the plate!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest4.Summary">The Cookies discover an old cutting board... which is actually a picture of Cookies who used to work for the House of Danish. The team learns of the family\'s history... and how it fell to ruin.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest5.Summary">Walnut is forcing the bellhop to exercise. In exchange for the bellhop\'s freedom, Walnut proposes a competition of strength. And guess who\'s accepted the challenge? GINGERBRIGHT!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest6.Summary">The team discovers another painting, this time showing the three greatest treasures of House Danish. The Cookies decide to continue their mission to defeat the bandits.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest7.Summary">Miss Scarab is terrified of Peanut, who challenges Strawberry Cookie to a battle of... cuteness? Strawberry Cookie may be shy, but she won\'t give up on her quest to rescue the guests!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest8.Summary">Another painting was hidden behind a mirror. A young Marble Danish Cookie and another Cookie are portrayed. After a brief history lesson from Marble Danish Cookie, the team continues with their mission.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest9.Summary">The Cookies have saved all of the staff and guests! The manager insists on expressing his gratitude with a gift... But he needs the Cookies to find it for him.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch02.SQuest10.Summary">The team is presented with a Golden Key from the manager, but the leader of the Apricot Jam Syndicate, Sachertorte Cookie, appears! Our friends finally learn more about the feud between Sachertorte Cookie and Marble Danish Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest01.Summary">The team is in hot pursuit of the bandits. An obstacle blocks their path, but nothing can stand in the way of teamwork and determination!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest02.Summary">The path forward is cleared, but Sachertorte Cookie appears once more! Our heroes charge forward to capture her, but fall into a trap and GingerBrave has been kidnapped!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest03.Summary">GingerBrave has been rescued, but Sachertorte Cookie, once more, has evaded capture. GingerBright proposes a plan to capture the bandits, but the room they\'re in is too messy to hold a strategy meeting.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest04.Summary">GingerBright\'s plan is laid out on the table, and everyone slowly agrees. Except for a mysterious voice that suddenly yells, NO!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest05.Summary">The mystery voice was Witchberry Cookie, who has appeared to tell our friends that they need a new plan that will actually prove useful. Or will it?</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest06.Summary">GingerBrave and Wizard Cookie run off to search for oil. The chef provides them with some top-notch olive oil as thanks for saving him and the hotel.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest07.Summary">GingerBright is looking for baby powder and runs into the bellhop and vault keeper. The two members of the staff are eager to help her and her friends with whatever they need.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest08.Summary">Strawberry Cookie and Marble Danish Cookie are in search of some sturdy rope and run into Miss Scarab. They don\'t see any rope, but with the help of Miss Scarab, the two procure a good length.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest09.Summary">The Cookies regroup with their procured supplies. But GingerBrave is suddenly curious... \"Do Marble Danish Cookie and Sachertorte Cookie really have to keep fighting?\"</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest10.Summary">The baby powder is used to distract the bandits, but Sachertorte Cookie buys time for her colleagues to escape. She\'s stronger than she looks!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest11.Summary">The Cookies manage to escape from the Apricot Jam rope thanks to covering themselves in oil. They use the rope from Miss Scarab to continue their pursuit.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest12.Summary">Sachertorte Cookie, with compass in hand, taunts the Cookies. Marble Danish Cookie charges forward to bring an end to their feud...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest13.Summary">Marble Danish Cookie finally realizes the truth after a reminder from Sachertorte Cookie, who was genuinely hurt by his past actions. He offers a sincere apology. Sachertorte Cookie disappears... but has left the compass!!! Has she forgiven him?</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest14.Summary">Despite being a family treasure, Marble Danish Cookie has decided to let the Cookies keep the compass. The compass points towards the Syrup Garden! Our friends embark on the next chapter of their adventure.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep02.Ch03.SQuest15.Summary">The group arrives at the Syrup Garden... but there\'s no syrup in sight! The garden is bone dry and barren. The Cookies decide to look for something to drink!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest01.Summary">Our friends find some syrup, but it was a trap! The team meets Radish Cookie, who is keeping watch over the garden all by herself!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest02.Summary">Radish Cookie tells our heroes about the situation she\'s in. The Syrup Garden was once teeming with life... The faucets were broken by the Churro Golem, which caused the garden to shrivel and wilt.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest03.Summary">Radish Cookie claims that syrup will flow once more if they fix one of the faucets and asks our heroes for help. The team is eager to help a Cookie in need!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest04.Summary">As soon as they fix the faucet, the Syrup Garden returns to life! The arid soil becomes healthy once more and residents start popping up from beneath the ground!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest05.Summary">The awakened farmers wish to thank our friends with a snack. They insist on it! Our friends decide to indulge as it\'s not polite to refuse!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest06.Summary">GingerBrave and friends tell Radish Cookie that they are searching for GingerDozer. Perhaps the leader of the garden, and Radish Cookie\'s sister, Rosemary Cookie, could help!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest07.Summary">The Churro Golem appears! Radish Cookie is shocked to see that the Churro Golem has broken the faucet once more. Our friends fend off the Churro Golem as Radish Cookie promises the team to take them to meet Rosemary Cookie at the Sweet Heart.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch01.SQuest08.Summary">The road to the Sweet Heart is no relaxing walk. The Churro Golem has broken a syrup pipe, which needs fixing!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest01.Summary">With another faucet fixed, more residents sprout from the ground! This time, they are vegetable residents!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest02.Summary">The cheerful Vegetable Residents decide to celebrate the garden\'s return to life with a party. Our friends join them at Sugar Beats Plaza.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest03.Summary">Sugar Beats Plaza has been abandoned for so long that it\'s in very rough shape. But not to worry! Our friends are eager to help restore the plaza to its former glory.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest04.Summary">The residents are ready to PAAARTY! Our friends decide to help the party\'s traditional conclusion of drinking syrup drops by finding more syrup.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest05.Summary">A small but very vocal Cheery Cherry Tomato is angry for being pulled out of the ground. Why? Well... According to her, fruit residents such as herself didn\'t want to be awakened...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest06.Summary">After seeing the Fruit Resident\'s reaction to being awakened, Radish Cookie begins to wonder if she\'s truly doing the right thing... Stay strong, Radish Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest07.Summary">Our friends have finally arrived at the Sweet Heart, which is being strangled by the Churro Golem\'s vines. The team hurriedly removes the vines to free Rosemary Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest08.Summary">The Sweet Heart is back in full operation, but the Churro Golem has appeared once more! He sure is persistent!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest09.Summary">Rosemary Cookie has awakened. But the joy of being reunited is short-lived, as Rosemary Cookie is shocked and aghast to see the garden revitalized. \"The Syrup Garden must not be awakened,\" she exclaims! What does she mean?!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch02.SQuest10.Summary">GingerBrave and friends chase after Rosemary Cookie and Radish Cookie. Why must the Syrup Garden not be awakened?!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.01.SQuest1.Summary">Witchberry Cookie is rummaging through bunches of clutter here and there. She asks that you clean the place up and help her find something very important.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.01.SQuest2.Summary">You discover a bundle of witchberries stored in a jar. Witchberry Cookie tells you a story about the castle\'s past.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.01.SQuest3.Summary">Witchberry Cookie has found what she\'s looking for! She wonders if other Cookies such as herself will ever be baked one day.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.01.SQuest4.Summary">In ages past, the castle was filled with many witches and their animal friends. Perhaps there are still traces of them around the castle?</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.01.SQuest5.Summary">Witchberry Cookie says that her dough is extra special due to a single, extra ingredient. She\'s not telling you what that secret ingredient is so easily...</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.02.SQuest1.Summary">The Apricot Jam Syndicate has returned to their hideout and decide to open a party to celebrate their latest haul. But they decide to clean up first. Hey, just because they\'re bandits doesn\'t mean their lair is filthy!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.02.SQuest2.Summary">It\'s not a real party without really tasty food! Walnut volunteers to cook for the night and reminisces about the first time meeting Sachertorte Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.02.SQuest3.Summary">Peanut is decorating the lair and reminisces with Sachertorte Cookie on how the Syndicate decided to create their emblem. After sharing a few words, Sachertorte Cookie disappears to... somewhere.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.02.SQuest4.Summary">The party is ready to begin! But where\'s Sachertorte Cookie? OH! There she is, and she\'s brought a special gift for the party?!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.02.SQuest5.Summary">Presents, memories, food, and cake! It\'s about time to get the party really started now!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.03.SQuest1.Summary">GingerBright is wandering around the castle and gets an amazing idea! She wants to try decorating a room herself, from start to finish! GingerBright eagerly asks Strawberry Cookie to join her.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.03.SQuest2.Summary">It seems that GingerBright has always had a soft spot for stale Cookies in jars... She wants them to feel comfy in her room.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.03.SQuest3.Summary">Lighting is an important element of interior design! GingerBright decides to hang up some cute curtains, but something\'s right outside the window?</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.03.SQuest4.Summary">GingerBright\'s masterpiece is almost complete, but there\'s something. OH! She thinks that having a plant in the room will be finishing cherry on top.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.03.SQuest5.Summary">The room is finally complete! GingerBright is extremely pleased with how the room turned out, but GingerBrave and Wizard Cookie are somewhat... hesitant to provide their honest opinions.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.04.SQuest1.Summary">The Juice Bar\'s bartender has called in sick! The Cheesemaster and Sparkling Cookie have come to the Juice Bar\'s aid... but there\'s some tension in the air.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.04.SQuest2.Summary">The two tavernmasters decide to find out whose beverage recipes are better. They invite Vampire Cookie to be an impartial judge.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.04.SQuest3.Summary">Let the judging commence! But according to Vampire Cookie, they\'re both too good to just choose one. I guess this round\'s a tie?</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.04.SQuest4.Summary">Round 2! Vampire Cookie tastes both entries, but cannot come to a decision. Sparkling Cookie and the Cheesemaster both agree to create a special beverage together!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.04.SQuest5.Summary">The ultimate beverage, created through teamwork, has been presented to Vampire Cookie... who has probably had too much juice tonight. Right before he falls asleep, he declares the competition a draw!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest1.Summary">Marble Danish Cookie is visited by a very nervous bellhop who has come to collect overdue fees for his hotel room, but he does not have enough funds. The bellhop suggests, carefully, that putting some items up for sale in the auction is an option to consider.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest2.Summary">The bellhop suggests to Marble Danish Cookie that a desk may be a suitable entry for the auction. Marble Danish Cookie suddenly becomes very angry and shares a history lesson with the bellhop.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest3.Summary">This time, the bellhop points at a chess piece for the auction, but alas, Marble Danish Cookie once more regales the bellhop with an even longer history lesson. All of his family treasures are too valuable and sentimental!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest4.Summary">Alas, there are very little options left. The bellhop suggests a portrait\'s frame and, as expected, Marble Danish Cookie refuses to be separated from it.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest5.Summary">In the end, Marble Danish Cookie is kicked out of the Grand Cabinet Hotel... While wallowing in self-pity, he is shocked to see the bellhop looking for him! Thanks to the bellhop\'s pleas to the manager, Marble Danish Cookie can stay in the hotel, but only until the auction... where a certain compass is up for grabs.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.06.SQuest1.Summary">Devil Cookie has decided to \"redecorate\" Angel Cookie\'s room. But Angel Cookie has returned a bit too soon!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.06.SQuest2.Summary">Devil Cookie has somehow ended up cleaning the mess they caused. The mischievous Cookie decides to make a run for it but...</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.06.SQuest3.Summary">The first escape attempt has failed! Devil Cookie makes up an excuse, but Angel Cookie misunderstands and is convinced that Devil Cookie is ready to become a kinder, nicer Cookie and suggest they go through the Portal to the Heavens together.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.06.SQuest4.Summary">No matter what happens, Devil Cookie is unwilling to pass through the magical portal! The Cookie suddenly feigns illness to escape!</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.06.SQuest5.Summary">Right before making an escape, Angel Cookie has figured out the truth. Devil Cookie puts on an amazing acting display and manages to finally escape.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest1">Family Heirlooms</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest2">How about that Desk?</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest3">Or this Chess Piece?</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest4">Or that Picture Frame?</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.05.SQuest5">Pathfinder\'s Last Compass</string>
