  <string name="$SpecialStory.07.SQuest1.Summary">The Shadow Witch, fixated on her research into the First Batch, has come across GingerDozer. But poor GingerDozer can\'t stop crying in fear, which is slowly putting the Shadow Witch on edge...</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.07.SQuest2.Summary">Sheriff Whiskerton, eager to please, and calm down, the Shadow Witch, has decided to clean up the room. He comes across a peculiar picture from the Shadow Witch\'s past.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.07.SQuest3.Summary">The Shadow Witch goes into a lecture about why she always wears her goggles when baking. Just as things were getting too dull for Sheriff Whiskerton, GingerDozer starts crying once more.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.07.SQuest4.Summary">GingerDozer won\'t stop crying despite the efforts of the Shadow Witch and Sheriff Whiskerton. In her anger, she plots more and more reckless ideas and the Sheriff decides to stop her before she regrets it.</string>
  <string name="$SpecialStory.07.SQuest5.Summary">After reading a passage in her recipe book, the Shadow Witch learns of methods to preserve dough. She orders Sheriff Whiskerton to store him in the fridge for safekeeping...</string>
