  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Floor.001.Story">When warm light envelops this sculpture of First Cream Cookie, it feels like you will remember something important, that you had previously forgotten... But what could it be, and what is this subtle feeling of desperation accompanying it?</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Floor.002.Story">It was thanks to First Cream Cookie that Mount St. Crème became a sacred and fresh sanctuary. Alas, it seems like it those days are gone.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Floor.003.Story">A beautiful handrail decorated with fully bloomed Creambloom flowers. It does a good job separating two parts of a room.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Floor.004.Story">A large urn filled with pretty creambloom flowers. This would make for a great addition to an elegant room!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Floor.005.Story">A simple, yet elegant candlestick. It exudes a divine aura.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Floor.006.Story">A puffy stool made out of fresh cream. You feel your energy recharge the moment you sit down in this!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Hanger.001.Story">A table as fresh as the items placed on top of it. Let\'s put this to good use!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Hanger.002.Story">An organ made with sweet whipped cream. When played, the tunes are just as smooth and fresh as you would expect from the instrument\'s appearance.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Wall.001.Story">Stained glass with a blinding warm light shining through. Looking at it reminds you of an old story.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Wall.002.Story">When you look at the soft light shining through, it kind of feels like someone you miss is talking to you...</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Wall.003.Story">Cream stairs decorated with a red velvet carpet. Walking on this will make you feel like the star of the show!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Ceil.001.Story">A golden ceiling-mounted fixture with a beautiful gemstone hanging at the bottom. What a find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Ceil.002.Story">A bird cage housing a cute little Cream Roll Bird. Some would rather it gets to fly freely in the sky, but in here it will live a long, safe life.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Ceil.003.Story">A chandelier that fills First Cream Cookie\'s room with a soft, sacred light.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Rug.001.Story">A fluffy rug made out of buttercream. Avoid spilling any liquid on it, as cleaning it is an arduous process.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.WP.001.Story">A warm wallpaper that emits a pleasant fragrance.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2001.Deck.001.Story">This elegant floor is so soft that any walking style would turn into a form of sneaking when it\'s walked on.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep03.Ch04.SQuest08.Summary">Our friends have arrived to Mount St. Crème, but it\'s a much scarier and unpleasant place than they expected!</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest01.Summary">Somewhere in Mount St. Crème, Onyx Cream Cookie shares news of the lukewarm winds and the appearance of a \"small Cookie\" to First Cream Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest02.Summary">The group has barely escaped from the unknown monstrosity. They need to find GingerDozer, but don\'t know where to go. If only they could use the compass once more...</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest03.Summary">GingerBrave and friends decide to ask for directions, but the residents seem ill. They decide to help the sickened residents before asking questions.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest04.Summary">Our heroes managed to temporarily cure the ill residents from their mold with baking soda. They learn that there\'s some sort of settlement close by.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest05.Summary">The Cookies are about to be swarmed by spores of some kind...! Onyx Cream Cookie appears and saves them. Our friends decide to help Onyx Cream Cookie\'s effort to fix the temperature controller.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest06.Summary">The temperature controller has been repaired! Our heroes make way to the Crème Refuge to see if they can finally get some information on GingerDozer\'s whereabouts.</string>
  <string name="$Journal.Ep04.Ch01.SQuest07.Summary">Many residents of Mount St. Crème suffer from mold. They approach the closed gates of the Crème Refuge... But a monster has appeared! In a blinding flash of light, First Cream Cookie has appeared to save everyone!</string>
