  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.001.Story">No one is allowed past this gate without permission. If an intruder attempts to breach the gate, the fork attached above is triggered to drop. Scary! Actually, not really... According to one of the guards, the fork is just there for decoration purposes only.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.002.Story">A wall from where one can keep watch. It\'s very secure too.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.003.Story">An impenetrable wall used to secure an area. Have we mentioned it\'s very sturdy?</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.004.Story">A frozen spire with a window. Let\'s put it to good use!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.005.Story">A small mushroom growing atop a patch of moss. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.006.Story">A mushroom growing atop a patch of moss! What an interesting find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Floor.007.Story">A skull covered in jam. Creepy...!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Wall.001.Story">A lone watchtower where one can keep watch. It\'s really sturdy.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Wall.002.Story">A lookout post covered in snow. Watch your step!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Wall.003.Story">A stony mountain with a sharp peak. Looks intimidating!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Wall.004.Story">A stony mountain with a snow-capped peak. Looks amazing!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Wall.005.Story">A very tall, stony mountain with a steep peak. Nature is awesome!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Ceil.001.Story">A giant icicle, cold to the touch. Be careful when walking below this thing!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Ceil.002.Story">A small icicle, cold to the touch. Be careful when walking below this thing!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.WP.001.Story">A frozen wall. Let\'s place it here and there.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.ExpirationDateCheckpoint.Deck.001.Story">A patch of ground covered in mold and fungus. Let\'s place it here and there, with caution.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.001.Story">A specialized bed used to stave off expiration. It\'s used for emergency situations, especially for those on the brink of their expiration date. You need to use the sleeping bag instead of coming into direct contact with the ice, otherwise you might get frostbite!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.002.Story">An industrial-grade fan used to cool an area. It serves its purpose.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.003.Story">An emergency radio that only broadcasts news and public announcements. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.004.Story">A collection of frozen rocks. These will look great wherever you decide to put them.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.005.Story">An emergency ice kit used to stave off spoilage. A must-have!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.006.Story">A cot used in emergency shelters to administer first aid. It\'s comfier than you think!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Floor.007.Story">A makeshift stool made from a mayonnaise bottle\'s cap. It serves its purpose.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Wall.001.Story">This rapid-freeze, industrial-grade freezer is used to store ice packs and ice cubes. Both Cookies and residents step into this unit whenever they need to cool down.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Wall.002.Story">Milk bottles that guarantee long-lasting freshness. Who wouldn\'t like to have these?!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Wall.003.Story">The freshest eggs ever. Everyone loves these!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Ceil.001.Story">An ice-pack fastened onto the ceiling. This will look great wherever you decide to put it.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Ceil.002.Story">A stalactite with water dripping downwards. Let\'s place it here and there.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Ceil.003.Story">A specialized thermometer used to specifically measure cold temperatures only. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Rug.001.Story">A puddle. And it\'s wet. Caution: slippery floor.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.WP.001.Story">An insulated wall that keeps things cold. Try decorating the wall with this to keep things cool.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CreamResidentShelter.Deck.001.Story">An insulated floor that keep things cold. Try decorating the floor with this to keep things cool.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Floor.001.Story">A two-tiered plate carrying all sorts of frozen goods and ice packs. Everything within is protected by a glass cloche. You might want to partner-up with a friend before opening this thing or you might get trapped inside!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Floor.002.Story">A workbench used to harvest and pack ice. It works very well!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Floor.003.Story">A frozen water bottle. Let\'s place it here and there.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Floor.004.Story">A bundle of ice and small ice packs. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Floor.005.Story">A pile of stale ice from some old sorbet. Still looks scrumptious! Sort of...</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Floor.006.Story">Harvesting in progress! The ice hasn\'t been put into a pack yet.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Wall.001.Story">A small area to rest after harvesting ice. Let\'s put it to good use!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Ceil.001.Story">An ice cube tray that contains colorful, frozen juice. Who wouldn\'t like to have this?!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Ceil.002.Story">A stalactite of ice cream. It goes well wherever you place it!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Ceil.003.Story">Two stalactites of ice cream. Let\'s place it here and there.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.WP.001.Story">A solid sheet of ice. Try decorating the walls with these.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.chillingmine.Deck.001.Story">A solid sheet of ice. Try decorating the floor with these.</string>
  <string name="$Room.Ep04.Blueprint.03">Crème Refuge</string>
  <string name="$Room.Ep04.Blueprint.04">Chilled Alcove</string>
  <string name="$Room.Ep04.Blueprint.05">Expiration Checkpoint</string>
  <string name="$Room.Ep04.Blueprint.03.Story">As the winds of Mount St. Crème have become saturated with humidity, mold and decay has spread at a frightening pace. The refuge was built in order to prolong freshness in these warm times, with ice packs being distributed to those on the brink of expiration.</string>
  <string name="$Room.Ep04.Blueprint.04.Story">This alcove is filled with leftover jelly beans, half-empty bottles of water, and stale ice cream. But mostly everything is either unusable or moldy... except for the ice packs! These precious ice packs can only be found here! Hopefully, there aren\'t any frozen jelly beans inside them...</string>
  <string name="$Room.Ep04.Blueprint.05.Story">A checkpoint to ensure the refuge does not fall victim to mold or decay. Therefore, only residents who haven\'t reached past their expiration date are allowed entry. None have managed to sneak past this tightly secured point of entry.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.001">Radiant Golden Fireplace</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.008">Navy Blue Velvet Stool</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.009">Heavy Iron Torch</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Wall.002">Onyx Cream Family Crest</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Ceil.001">Historical Stone Arch</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.006">Rustic Chair</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Rug.001">Elegant Rug</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.005">Recreational Table</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Ceil.003">Warm-Glowing Lamp</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.007">Robust Pillar</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.002">Radiant Silvery Fireplace</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.004">Cozy Ottoman</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Wall.001">Snow Peltered Window</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.003">Stylish Decorative Pillars</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Ceil.002">Candle Chandelier</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.WP.001">Strong Brick Wall</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Deck.001">Decorative Floor</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.001.Story">This radiant fireplace burns bright and hot no matter how cold it is outside. Sitting in front of it brings a sensation of warmth and comfort that no other fireplaces can give.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.008.Story">A tiny velvet stool, in navy blue. It serves its purpose.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.009.Story">A heavy torch made from iron. This will look great wherever you decide to put it.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Wall.002.Story">The crest of the Onyx Cream family. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Ceil.001.Story">This arch is steeped in history. Just looking at it makes you feel like you are home.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.006.Story">A simple and pragmatic chair. This will look great wherever you decide to put it.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Rug.001.Story">An elegant but cozy rug. What a lucky find!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.005.Story">A table used for games and recreation. Who wouldn\'t like to have this?!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Ceil.003.Story">A lamp that gives off a soft, warm glow. Let\'s place it somewhere!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.007.Story">A solid pillar. Let\'s put it here and there.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.002.Story">A silvery fireplace with a crackling, pale fire. It looks cold and eerie, but the closer you get, the more you feel at home.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.004.Story">An ottoman that is soft, comfy, and elegantly decorated. You could sit on this for hours without feeling the need to get up!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Wall.001.Story">From this window, you can view the snow from the warmth of your room. As the winds pick up, you can hear the snow peltering the window. Sitting by this window and watching the snowstorm somehow calms your mind.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Floor.003.Story">An impressively decorated pillar featuring the Onyx Cream family crest. It\'s fancy, but not flashy. It\'s sturdy, but not bulky. And it goes well with anything in any room.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Ceil.002.Story">A chandelier of candles embraces the room with a warm glow. Be careful not to neglect it though as the candles may be extinguished on a windy day. Though it can be a chore, Onyx Cream Cookie adores this chandelier and the warmth it radiates.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.WP.001.Story">Through ice and snow, wind and storm, these walls are built to withstand anything. This solid brick wall is capable of insulating heat in the harshest of cold snaps as well. Rest assured, you\'ll always be shielded from the cold at night as you fall asleep.</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2007.Deck.001.Story">A decorative floor chosen by Onyx Cream Cookie himself. It\'s an elegant yet uncomplicated pattern, much like the Cookie himself.</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep04.07">By Her Command</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep04.07.Story">Our friends have officially teamed up with Onyx Cream Cookie, who is eager to restore Mount St. Crème to its former glory. What fuels his courage and loyalty?</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep04.08">Fizzy Soda: Weakling No More</string>
  <string name="$Collection.Memory.Album.Ep04.08.Story">Fizzy Soda was always concerned that he\'d lose his carbonation. But no more! The change of climate has tremendously transformed the region and himself!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.Main">Boring, Boring, Boooring Violin Solo</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.01">Who Wrote That Song?</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.02">The Story Behind the Music</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.03">Mint Choco Cookie\'s Recital</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.01.Summary">Devil Cookie happens to hear a bit of Mint Choco Cookie\'s solo violin piece and claims it\'s BORING! But, uh-oh, the composer of the piece is none other than Mint Choco Cookie himself!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.02.Summary">Devil Cookie tries to make amends, but Mint Choco Cookie enters into a deep monologue on the history of his composed piece.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Title.03.Summary">In the end, Mint Choco Cookie performs a concert in Devil Cookie\'s room... What an interesting but heartwarming apology, Devil Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.Main">Midsummer Snow</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.01">Summer Heat is Exhausting</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.02">Midsummer Snow</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.03">A Cookie who Loves Cold and Snow</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.01.Summary">Onyx Cream Cookie has provided his room to shelter a few Moldizens. However, the summer heat has made his usually comfortable room rather warm. Is there a way to provide a chillier environment?</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.02.Summary">Onyx Cream Cookie has requested the aid of Snow Sugar Cookie. As Snow Sugar Cookie waves their magic wand, it suddenly begins to snow!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Title.03.Summary">As he gazes upon the falling snow, Onyx Cream Cookie is reminded of a certain Cookie, one who resembles the pure white snow.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.Main">Time to Laugh, Blackberry Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.01">Make Blackberry Cookie Laugh!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.02">How About... THIS!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.03">Time to Depart</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.01.Summary">Avocado Cookie has decided that today will be the day she will make Blackberry Cookie laugh!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.02.Summary">Blackberry Cookie remains unphased, especially because she\'s already heard the jokes that were prepared. Avocado Cookie only has one more joke up her sleeve... Will it work?!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Title.03.Summary">Alas, Blackberry Cookie does not laugh. How many jokes will it take to finally get a reaction from her?</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.Main">Finding Adventurer Cookie</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.01">Summoning Magic!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.02">Summoning Failed?!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.03">Fine, I\'ll do it Myself</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.01.Summary">Adventurer Cookie is never home, and Blackberry Cookie is seeking a way to find him. Wizard Cookie attempts to use a summoning spell to find the wandering explorer!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.02.Summary">The summoning spell worked! Sort of... Instead of Adventurer Cookie, the spell has summoned Alchemist Cookie, who also has an idea to solve the problem of Adventurer Cookie\'s constant running away.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Title.03.Summary">Alchemist Cookie wants to create a potion to keep Adventurer Cookie at home, but Wizard Cookie is adamant that he can make the spell work. As usual, the two enter into a heated argument of magic vs. alchemy.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Illust.Dialog.01">I am the composer.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0023.Illust.Dialog.02">HAHA- What?
... Oh.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Illust.Dialog.01">It isn\'t an exaggeration
to say that you\'ve
saved the day.</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.2007.Illust.Dialog.02">Aw, I\'m glad to have helped!
And besides, I got to meet
some new friends!</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Illust.Dialog.01">How would you, Blackberry Cookie,
say hello to a fish underwater?</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0113.Illust.Dialog.02">...</string>
  <string name="$UX.CPC.cookie.0025.Illust.Dialog.01">I will have to look for
Adventurer Cookie myself.</string>
  <string name="$Script_EP4_CH2_SQ3_CUT1_Npc.0046_1">RAAAWR!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0023_1">What is that noise? Who\'s making that racket?
Is that SUPPOSED to be music?!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0023_2">Eh...?
A soft and wistful violin piece like that is...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0023_3">BORING!!!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0023_4">HEY! YOU WITH THE VIOLIN!
Who are you and why are you playing such boring music?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0046_5">Ah, hello there, Devil Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0046_6">I guess you did not enjoy the solo piece I was playing.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0023_7">Mint Choco Cookie!
No one likes listening to such dreary and sad music! Who in their right mind would write such a slow and dreary song?!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0046_8">I am the composer.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_1_POR1_Cookie.0023_9">HAHA- What?
... Oh.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_1">HEHEHE! You know I was joking, right...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_2">Of course, Devil Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_3">Well, okay then... Then I-</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_4">The title of this piece is \"The Lonely Musician.\" It\'s a solo violin piece that was composed during a prolonged period of difficulty.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_5">Eh...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_6">There was an unusually violent storm that night... I still remember the cold raindrops mercilessly pounding against the castle\'s walls.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_7">Everyone took refuge to warm and cozy spots throughout the castle. But I continued to perform outside, risking sogginess.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_8">Mint... Choco Cookie...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_9">Would you like to know why I continued to perform that night, Devil Cookie?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_10">Eh? Wait, no-</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_11">I wanted to reach someone, anyone with my music. To have them hear my violin, hear my soul. As a musician without a stage, I had no choice but to continue performing in the rain.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_12">So I endured that ferocious storm. The rain had drenched my violin, muffling its usual effervescent strings. And yet, I kept hoping that someone would listen.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_13">Hey, can we like, stop this conversation and-</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_14">This solo was composed as a reminder of my struggle. Perhaps it resonated with you on a certain level, my friend.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0046_15">Slow, dreary, and melancholy.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_2_POR1_Cookie.0023_16">STAAAHP!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0046_1">Ladies and gentlemen, I would like to welcome everyone to this small concert of mine.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0046_2">Before I begin, I\'d like to introduce and thank our wondrous host, who has allowed us to use this amazing space for my performance.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0046_3">A warm round of applause for our host, Devil Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0023_4">Stop clapping! No compliments! Don\'t cheer! QUIET!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0046_5">Now then. Shall we begin?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0046_6">The first piece is a solo violin sonata I composed myself. It is titled, \"A Lonely Musician.\"</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0023_3_POR1_Cookie.0023_7">START CLAPPING EVERYONE! Clap your hands! Applaud! You\'re about to witness the greatest violin solo ever!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Cookie.2007_1">Hurry, come inside! It\'s much cooler in here.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Npc.0041_2">Oh...? This is...
Is this your room, Sir Onyx Cream Cookie?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Npc.0040_3">It\'s... not so different from the temperature outside...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Cookie.2007_4">I thought it would be an acceptable temperature, but it seems that there is no beating the summer heat...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Npc.0039_5">Urgh...
My entire body is itchy because of the mold...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Npc.0040_6">It\'ll only spread more if we don\'t find a place to cool down...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Cookie.2007_7">It seems I must find another answer to this predicament.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Cookie.2007_8">Please wait here. Keep movement to a minimum, otherwise you will just be warming yourselves up.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Cookie.2007_1">Over here! There are residents who need aid, immediately!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Npc.0039_2">Sir Onyx Cream Cookie...? Who\'re you talking to...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_1_POR1_Cookie.0030_3">Hello. Nice to meet you!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Cookie.2007_4">Everyone, say hello to Snow Sugar Cookie. I\'ve asked for their help.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Npc.0040_5">A Cookie? How can a Cookie help us...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Npc.0041_6">Hey! That\'s not very nice!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Cookie.0030_7">I don\'t know if I\'ll be of much help... But I\'ll try my best...!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Cookie.0030_8">I heard that you like winter and snow, just like me!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Npc.0041_9">Huh? What\'s happening? Why is that thing you\'re holding glowing blue?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Npc.0039_10">Do you feel that?! There\'s a cold breeze coming from over there!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_2_POR1_Cookie.2007_11">I... I don\'t believe it! It\'s snowing?!
Fascinating...!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Npc.0039_1">Hugging the great Snow King is like... the best feeling ever. I don\'t feel as itchy as before!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Npc.0041_2">I wanna try too!
... Oh, wow... I feel so much better!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.2007_3">Calm down, everyone! The Snow King may not like being crowded!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.0030_4">It\'s okay! I think the Snow King is happy to meet new friends.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Npc.0040_5">Hehe! Then does that mean I can scooch in closer?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.2007_6">Thank you, Snow Sugar Cookie. I believe it isn\'t an exaggeration to say that you\'ve saved the day.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.0030_7">Aw, I\'m glad to have helped! And besides, I got to meet some new friends!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.0030_8">But erm... It looks like something was bothering you earlier, Onyx Cream Cookie. Is something wrong?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.2007_9">...!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.2007_10">It\'s nothing. The cold breeze and snow just... made me think of...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie2007_3_POR1_Cookie.2007_11">of someone.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cooie0042_1">I thought you called me to help organize your forge.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cooie0042_2">And yet, it seems that was not the case.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cookie0113_3">HAHA! You caught me!
Today is the day I\'m finally gonna make you laugh!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cooie0042_4">Is that so? Then please, make it quick, for I\'ve more urgent matters at the mansion.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cookie0113_5">Alrighty! But where\'re my manners?! Take a seat and make yourself at home!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cookie0113_6">Ah? Not on the anvil... it\'s not the most comfortable of places to sit, haha!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cooie0042_7">...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cookie0113_8">Now, get ready to laugh so hard, you\'ll end up crying!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_1_POR1_Cookie0113_9">Just you wait!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cookie0113_1">What does a sick apple tell the doctor?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cooie0042_2">\"I\'m not PEELING well.\"
You told me this exactly 231 days ago.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cookie0113_3">Did I? HAHA!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cookie0113_4">Then how \'bout this!
What is the only fruit that has a neck?
NECTARINES! Hahaha!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cooie0042_5">That too has already been repeated on many occasions.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cookie0113_6">Hmmm... Those two didn\'t cut it, eh...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cooie0042_7">Now, if I may, I must return to the mansion.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cookie0113_8">Wait! Not so fast! I\'ve still got one more for ya!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_2_POR1_Cooie0042_9">...
Then by all means, but with haste, please.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cookie0113_1">How would you, Blackberry Cookie, say hello to a fish underwater?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cooie0042_2">But excessive exposure to water would lead to sogginess.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cookie0113_3">Blub, blub, blub, I\'m Blubberry Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cooie0042_4">...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cookie0113_5">Huh... I thought that one would definitely do the trick.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cooie0042_6">I really must return to the mansion now.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cooie0042_7">Until next time, Avocado Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cookie0113_8">Not even a single smile...!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cookie0113_9">Oh well! I\'ll get her to laugh next time, I know it!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0113_3_POR1_Cookie0113_10">One day, I will definitely make her laugh!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_1">So...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_2">You came here to ask if I could figure out where Adventurer Cookie is right now?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_3">It sounds like you need a detective, not a wizard...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_4">As I was organizing some old documents and books...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_5">I found a book on something called \"summoning magic.\"</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_6">I assumed that, as a wizard, you would be familiar with it.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_7">Oh?! Summoning magic? Is that what I think it-</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_8">No, no, wait! Let me look it up myself first!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_9">He seems... extremely excited.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_10">Ah! Here we are! The \"Summoning Spell to Summon Anything!\"</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_11">... A rather odd and suspicious name.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_12">Now, let me see here... First, I need to picture a specific characteristic of Adventurer Cookie in my head. His hat, maybe? And then, I open this up and...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_13">It has started to glow...
Perhaps this will truly work.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_14">Okay! And now... the incantation... I SUMMON THEE!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie.0025_15">HYAH!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_16">...!
It worked.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cookie0034_17">What?! Where? HUH?
I was in my lab and now... WHAT?!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_1_POR1_Cooie0042_18">But this is not the Cookie we seek.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cookie.0025_1">I... may have confused who wears what sort of hat...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cookie0034_2">Uh, HELLO!? Will someone tell me what\'s going on here?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cooie0042_3">I have requested Wizard Cookie to locate Adventurer Cookie through the means of magic.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cookie.0025_4">I tried to cast a spell while picturing Adventurer Cookie in my head...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cookie0034_5">And let me guess, it was me who was summoned, not him?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cooie0042_6">Yes.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cookie0034_7">Hm... OH!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cookie0034_8">I think I know a surefire method of finding Adventurer Cookie and keeping him at home!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_2_POR1_Cooie0042_9">Oh?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie0034_1">We can use alchemy to transmute Adventurer Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie0034_2">Just imagine! He actually stays at home like a responsible Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie0034_3">There\'d be no need to worry about him gallivanting outside the mansion anymore!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie.0025_4">But that\'s not Adventurer Cookie! That sounds like a sham!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie.0025_5">Besides, I already know what went wrong with the incantation. It\'ll work this time, I know it!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie0034_6">An alchemical transmutation of a Cookie...! It\'s genius!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie.0025_7">ARE YOU LISTENING?!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_8">It seems they are both living in their own worlds...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_9">Oh? Wizard Cookie\'s spellbook has fallen onto the floor.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_10">"The accuracy of this spell has been calculated to be... 0.00001%."</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_11">"Use for entertainment and recreation only."</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_12">I think I shall depart.</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie0034_13">Hey, can I write down my formula here?</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cookie.0025_14">No! You are NOT ALLOWED to write anything about alchemy in my spellbook!</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_15">They truly are living in their own worlds...</string>
  <string name="$Script_PuzzleChallenge_Cookie0025_3_POR1_Cooie0042_16">I will have to look for Adventurer Cookie myself.</string>
