  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.WP.001">Smooth Lacquer Wall</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Deck.001">Smooth Lacquer Floor</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.001.Story">A large flower pot filled with buckwheat noodles. This pot, decorated with sparkling gold dust, was apparently partly made by Buckwheat Cookie herself. The flowers adorning the noodles inside are sprinkled with dew drops, giving them an even fresher appearance!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.002.Story">A large flower pot filled with buckwheat noodles. The jade-colored pot makes the food inside look even more appetizing than usual. But even so, it\'s purely for decoration, so don\'t get any ideas!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.003.Story">A skillfully crafted bed that lets air flow through, keeping your body crispy and cool even during hot summer days.</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.004.Story">A repurposed side dish container that\'s now being used as a storage cabinet. Thrifty, yet stylish!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.005.Story">Few have seen the beautiful design of this desk, as it seems to always be filled by endless amounts of work. Let\'s place it somewhere and start taking care of it, one scroll at a time!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.006.Story">A dressing table made out of a bowl? Simply... Soup-erb!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.007.Story">A hanger made out of spare chopsticks. With this, you can alleviate some of the burden of your laundry chair!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Floor.008.Story">A teapot with pretty red flowers painted on the side. The perfect addition for a relaxing afternoon!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Wall.001.Story">A large window with a view of the waning moon outside. Buckwheat Cookie says she often sits in front of this window late at night, lost in thought. Maybe one day, she will get to tell someone about how beautiful the moon is.</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Wall.002.Story">A shelf made for storing hair accessories. Let\'s put it up somewhere easy to reach!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Ceil.001.Story">A light green see-through curtain made out of radish. While it may not block sunlight, it does a great job at keeping the room humid and fragrant, while also being a beautiful piece of decoration!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Ceil.002.Story">Traditional lanterns hanging from the ceiling. Let\'s find a suitable room for them!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Ceil.003.Story">Decorative balls of buckwheat noodles hanging on a string. It is a trendy piece of decoration that doubles as a conversation starter!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Rug.001.Story">A durable carpet made woven out of finely split bamboo. Let\'s find a good place to put it!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.WP.001.Story">A smooth wall with a square pattern. Add this to a room to give it a more elegant look!</string>
  <string name="$item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie2012.Deck.001.Story">Beautiful flooring that has been polished to give off a smooth shine. The lack of even a single speck of dust speaks volumes about the personality of its resident.</string>
  <string name="$Cookie.0106">Space Doughnut</string>
  <string name="$Cookie.0106.Story">Communication with this mysterious creature has proven to be a rather daunting task. Plus, they don\'t seem to remember where they came from and why.

However, nothing stops us from befriending this adorable being even though we don\'t share the same language. And it seems like the Space Doughnut has made a bunch of flat friends here already!</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0106.Ceil.999">Space Doughnut\'s Room Sign</string>
  <string name="$Item.Deco.CookieRoom.cookie0106.Ceil.999.Story">Welcome to Space Doughnut\'s Chaotic and Fantastic Room!</string>
  <string name="$Cookie.0106.Soulstone">Space Doughnut\'s Souldrop</string>
  <string name="$Cookie.0106.Soulstone.Tooltip">This mysterious drop holds a piece of Space Doughnut\'s soul. Just looking at it makes you want to du-doa! Prrrp-prprp!</string>
  <string name="$Room.Cookie.0106">Space Doughnut\'s Chaotic and Fantastic Room</string>
  <string name="$Room.Cookie.0106.Story">In Space Doughnut\'s room, colorful candies sparkle on the walls, and mysterious space music can be heard. If you peek into this chaotic yet fantastic room, you may get a glimpse of Space Doughnut\'s home, somewhere far, far away.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_1">...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_2">Madam First Grain Cookie...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_3">She always seems to be deep in thought recently.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Npc.0061_4">Pardon me, Madam First Grain Cookie, but it appears that this season\'s harvest has not been as plentiful as we\'d hoped.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_5">Perhaps there are a few more bushels that haven\'t arrived yet. My dear Moletatoes! Could you go and check, please?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Npc.0063_6">Check for more bushels! Check, check, and haul!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Npc.0064_7">Haul! Haul! Heave ho, heave ho!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Npc.0061_8">Ah! Everything appears to be in proper order now! Thank you, Madam First Grain Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_9">No need to thank me, dear.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_10">*Sigh*</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_11">Another heavy sigh...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_12">Is it because of...?
... I need to do something!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_13">Madam First Grain Cookie!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_14">Hello, my dear Chickpea Cookie! Is something wrong? How may I-</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_15">Madam First Grain Cookie. You wish to see Yummers, don\'t you? You should go pay a visit!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_16">Pardon? I don\'t know what you-</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_17">You seem awfully lethargic lately. And I have noticed you seem to be sighing much more often of late.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_18">Since order has been restored to the Temple of Abundance...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_19">Why not take this opportunity to pay a visit? I am certain things will remain fine even in your absence.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_20">But... If something were to happen to the temple...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_21">Everything shall be right as rain.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_22">We shall all keep a watchful eye on the temple until you return.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_23">Chickpea Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_24">Thank you so very much, deary. Then I shall heed your advice and pay a brief visit.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_25">But...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_26">Perhaps I should finish up my own chores and tasks before departing.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2013_27">Chores, madam?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_28">Yes, chores! Weeding and harvesting!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ1_POR1_Cookie.2011_29">No need to dawdle! Chop chop, let\'s get going!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_1">My, oh my! So this is Mount St. Crème.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_2">Hmmm...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_3">Where is Yummers...? Should I ask for directions?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie2001_4">Who are you...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_5">Oh my! What lovely timing. I was just wondering if I could ask you for some dir-</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_6">Ah.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie2001_7">\???</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_8">You are...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie2001_9">Have... have we met...?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_10">... You do not recognize me?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie2001_11">My apologies.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie2001_12">I have no recollection of anything before I... woke up here.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_13">Oh deary, deary... I found myself in a similar predicament when I first woke up as well.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_14">But to hear that she has completely forgotten everything is... Well, it\'s a shame.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_15">... No, not a shame. It\'s disheartening.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie2001_17">...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_18">Now, now! No need to frown. I can\'t bear to say anything with that expression on your face!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_19">Perhaps... Nothing can be done...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_20">No. What you did for me in ages past... now, it\'s my turn.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_21">Shall we start anew then? As it is our first time meeting in this setting, we can introduce ourselves for the first time here too.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_22">I am First Grain Cookie, and I am here to visit Yummers.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_23">This time, allow me to provide guidance.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_24">I am glad to have met you... Back then and here now.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_25">I truly am...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ2_POR1_Cookie.2011_26">From the bottom of my heart...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_1">I see...
Hm, First Egg Cookie...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_2">We must act with caution.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_3">I have also encountered First Egg Cookie...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_4">But why would she behave in such a manner?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_5">I do not know, but I\'ve a rising suspicion she wishes to exploit the Cookies of the First Batch with malicious intent.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_6">And it is likely she will not stop with the First Batch...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_7">Given what I know of her... You are no doubt her final target.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_8">But I shall not burden you with such concerns at this moment...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_9">Such talk is dreadfully dreary, is it not? Perhaps a change of subject! Tell me, have you met other Cookies?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_10">Yes. Onyx Cream Cookie is a good friend, and recently, one called GingerBrave.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_11">Ahha! Am I correct to assume you\'ve made more friends beyond those two?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_12">What about the others? The other First Cookies?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_13">I... You are the only one, aside from First Egg Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_14">Deary, deary me! I am quite honored to hear so!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_15">I still remember the first day we met.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_16">... I am sorry.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_17">Oh? For what?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie2001_18">I... I wish I could remember who you are.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_19">Dear, dear, it\'ll come back to you someday. And besides, in the meantime, I can remember our past for the both of us for now.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Event.0002_20">Frst Grn Cookie? (First Grain Cookie?)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Event.0002_21">Iz tht rlly yu? (Is that really you?)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_22">Dearest Yummers! It\'s so good to see you again, my dear!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Event.0002_23">Ar yu hre ta see me? (Are you here to see me?)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Cookie.2011_24">Of course I am, little one! Oh, how I\'ve missed you so!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Event.0002_25">I mssd yu too! I thert I reconzed yr voe! (I missed you too! I thought I recognized your voice!)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ3_POR1_Event.0001_26">I\'m here too... Hehe!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Event.0002_1">Thers er ma snacks! (These are my snacks!)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Event.0001_2">And this is my pillow...!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Event.0002_3">Wr cn shr! Shrng iz crng! (We can share! Sharing is caring!)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Event.0001_4">Okay! You can sleep on half of my pillow, hehe.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_5">How adorable! They seem to have become the best of friends.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie2001_6">Yes, they have become inseparable.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_7">Some among us shared such a relationship as well...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie2001_8">Among... us?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_9">Sisters, in fact. First Salt Cookie and First Sugar Cookie were very close.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_10">Oh, and how could I forget First Sprinkle Cookie and First Yeast Cookie! Deary, deary, the trouble they\'d get into together.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_11">Ahhh... This reminds me of the good old days.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie2001_12">I...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_13">Now, now! No need to frown.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_14">Even my memory isn\'t fully intact.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_15">But perhaps all this talk of the past may help to spark some of those forgotten memories, for you and me both?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie2001_16">Yes, perhaps so.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_17">*Chuckle*
It\'s worth a shot, is it not?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_18">Ah! And if I were to encounter any other Cookies...</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_19">I promise to share as much as I can with you.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_20">The more stories I share, the faster your memory might come back!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2001_21">Thank you, First Grain Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ4_POR1_Cookie.2011_22">Deary, deary! There really is no need to thank me.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_1">Welp! Look at the time! I really must get going now.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Event.0002_2">Frst Grn Cookie! Ar ye leevng? (First Grain Cookie! Are you leaving?)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_3">Yes, I\'m afraid so. It\'s time for me to go home.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Event.0002_4">Wll yu b bak? (Will you be back?)</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_5">Of course I will, little one! Now, promise me that you\'ll stay best friends with GingerDozer and keep sharing your snacks too, okay?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Event.0002_6">OKAY!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_7">Ah, and First Cream Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie2001_8">Yes?</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_9">I shall return.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_10">Until then, I pray that you will fare well.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie2001_11">... Thank you.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie2001_12">I, too, pray that you will fare well.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie2001_13">I look forward to the day we shall meet again.</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_14">Oh me oh my!</string>
  <string name="$Script_SS12_SQ5_POR1_Cookie.2011_15">I couldn\'t have asked for a more perfect send-off!</string>
