  <string name="$Saga06_Ch1_sq1.Summary">The Court of Judgment bustles with another day of trials and verdicts. Outside its doors, a rally led by Saffron Cookie is in full swing. She has earned a reputation for sharing what she calls the truth of the Cookie world.

With each passing day, more and more Cookies find themselves drawn to listen. Many Cookies who heard her speak have set off on a journey... but none have returned. 

Inside the courtroom, the trials of Choco Gold Cookie and Roasted Salt Cookie proceed in turn, each met with a fair and fitting verdict from the impartial Scale of Good and Evil. Then, at laste, the trial of Saffron Cookie begins.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch1_sq2.Summary">The trial of Saffron Cookie is now underway. At the heart of the case: is Saffron Cookie responsible for the growing number of Cookies who have vanished? Saffron Cookie\'s defense is as calm as it is unsettling... She claims she did nothing more than speak at her gatherings, that she never abducted or confined anyone, and that every Cookie who left did so of their own free will. And if that is true, she argues, there is no crime to charge her with.

She goes even further, questioning whether the scales are even capable of weighing something like this, and whether if a court that cannot answer this question has any right to be passing judgment at all.

Can Saffron Cookie truly be found guilty? And at this very moment, crashing into the middle of it all is GingerBrave and friends, hot on the trail of another Cookie of the First Batch!</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch1_sq3.Summary">The trial came to an abrupt halt when GingerBrave and friends crashed the proceedings! Charged with contempt, but deemed not guilty enough for a serious sentencing, they were handed off to the perpetually overworked Supervisor of Records, Candy Chain Cookie, as temporary assistants. Their mission is to dig up everything they can on the deeply tangled case of Saffron Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch1_sq4.Summary">Meanwhile, Saffron Cookie is set to be confined to the Sugar Glass Dome pending further investigation and a final verdict. When her followers come to visit, she shares a few words to console them.
\"It\'s unfair to be persecuted for speaking the truth.\"
\"If the Absolute is watching, this injustice will not go unanswered.\"
\"The Absolute holds a power far greater than this broken courtroom could ever hope to wield.\"
... With words that seem to mean little on the surface, her followers suddenly depart with quiet purpose. To where, nobody knows...</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch2_sq1.Summary">Court resumes with the evidence and witnesses our heroes have managed to gather. Saffron Cookie maintains her innocence, insisting her only crime was sharing the truth out of a genuine desire of goodwill to see others flourish.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch2_sq2.Summary">The investigation seemingly backs up Saffron Cookie\'s claims. Not a single grain of malicious intent could be found. However, the fact remains: Cookies who had listened to her teachings have walked to the First Oven, and none have returned. Just as the trial seemed hopelessly deadlocked, one crucial piece of information surfaces... Saffron Cookie is connected to First Egg Cookie.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch2_sq3.Summary">A final piece of evidence uncovers a startling truth...! Saffron Cookie is connected to First Egg Cookie!
What could this mean? Is she being manipulated? Is Saffron Cookie, herself, also a victim?</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch2_sq4.Summary">The trial spirals deeper into uncertainty as the scales still refuses to budge. With no verdict in sight, it falls to First Salt Cookie and First Sugar Cookie to decide for themselves. Just as they are about to render judgment, a deafening crash shakes the entire courtroom.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch3_sq1.Summary">A massive human hand bursts through the Sugar Glass Dome. The hand belongs to none other than the Shadow Witch.

The moment the dome is shattered, a vision surfaces... hazy, dreamlike, belonging to no one and everyone at once.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch3_sq2.Summary">What surfaced was a memory... First Salt Cookie and First Sugar, back in their days as witches, weaving magic into a shimmering light that looked just like a Soul Jam. They believed the Cookies needed a Hero, and they had set out to make one themselves.

But there was no time to make sense of this vision of the past. While the two reel in confusion, the Shadow Witch\'s hand closes around the Cookie of the First Batch... and vanishes.

The Court of Judgment stands in ruins, paralyzed and unable to proceed with the trial.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch3_sq3.Summary">The truth begins to take shape and reveal itself. Saffron Cookie\'s teachings lured Cookies to the First Oven. The Shadow Witch, drawn by the spectacle, seized the opportunity to take the Cookie of the First Batch herself. To Saffron Cookie, this was proof that First Egg Cookie would soon have the First Batcher in hand. As for those who followed her teachings, they had taken one step closer to the truth.

She believes it still... even as First Egg Cookie never came for her.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch3_sq4.Summary">With the Sugar Glass Dome in ruins, and the First Batcher gone, the courtroom sits in shambles. Saffron Cookie\'s verdict remains undelivered as well. First Salt Cookie and First Sugar Cookie make their decision... The verdict is to be suspended until a wiser path forward can be found, one that does not rely solely on the scales.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch4_sq1.Summary">GingerBrave and our heroes declare they will not give up until they find and rescue the kidnapped First Batcher. They set off once more on their already long journey.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch4_sq2.Summary">Alone in the wreckage, First Salt Cookie and First Sugar Cookie walk slowly through what remains of the courtroom. With the chaos finally stilled, the memories come back in somewhat clearer fragments.

In their past human forms, First Cream Cookie reaching out to them, asking them to come along. First Egg Cookie and First Cream Cookie at odds, their disagreement sharp and unresolved. And then the moment that set everything in motion... the two quietly determined to give the Cookies a Hero, gazing at the Soul Jams the witches had forged first, and making a decision... \"We will make one too\".</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch4_sq3.Summary">And so, the sisters talk. They had once baked Cookies with purpose, creators who looked down upon the world they helped shape. But now that they themselves are Cookies as well, they realize it does not feel so different from the human world they left behind. Good and evil remain blurred at the edges. Even sweetness carries a trace of bitterness in every grain of flour.

In the quiet of the ruined courtroom, they take turns pondering over everything slowly. Have the verdicts they\'ve delivered, the criminals they\'ve judged and confined, and their decisions in the Court of Judgment truly contributed to making the Cookie World more beautiful?

They weigh their actions, both goodwill and neglect, on the scales and watch.

In the end... they finally understand. No one can save every world. And not everything can be neatly divided into black and white, guilty and innocent.</string>
  <string name="$Saga06_Ch4_sq4.Summary">The two accept the limits of the ideal world they have built. They had been denied by their own creation, the scales, and there was no longer any way to deny the limits that came with it.

First Salt Cookie &amp; First Sugar Cookie decide the wisest course of action is to longer interfere. The more they become involved, the more the world the Cookies have built may crumble. As they were once human, they will take a step back and let the will of Cookies reign free... The Cookies\' world and fate are to be shaped by their own hands.

And with that, everything is settled. Though the two declare they may not be able to escape the castle entirely, they know they must no longer confine themselves to the courtroom. They look back at the courtroom one last time. Cracks run through every wall and surface, threatening to come apart at any moment. For too long, they have stood in this place, weighing good and evil.

Finally, the step outside... carefully, quietly. For the first, they have crossed beyond the boundaries of their own domain to see the real world with their own eyes. Behind them, the close the courtroom door shut, its hinges barely hanging. The two of them walk toward a world they\'ve never truly seen...</string>
